<item>
            <title>[LU-20023] lnet: mark locked primary peer NI DOWN if removed by discovery</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20023</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If discovery removes a peer NI but &lt;tt&gt;lnet_peer_del_nid()&lt;/tt&gt; refuses&lt;br/&gt;
deletion (e.g. locked primary), the NI remains present, appears healthy,&lt;br/&gt;
and so may still be selected for TX.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Treat this as a discovery-driven DOWN event instead by calling&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;handle_disc_lpni_health()&lt;/tt&gt;. This preserves the NI for identity while&lt;br/&gt;
preventing its use for transmission.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
